@startuml 03-multi-device-registration
title Device Registration Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam shadowing false

skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #1976D2
    LifeLineBorderColor #1976D2
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
    ParticipantBorderColor #1976D2
}

actor "User\n(New Device)" as userNew
participant "New Device\nExtension" as newDev
actor "User\n(Existing Device)" as userExisting
participant "Existing Device\nExtension" as existingDev
participant "S3" as s3

== Step 1: New Device Setup ==

userNew -> newDev : Install extension
newDev -> newDev : Generate Device ID (UUID)
newDev -> newDev : Generate Ed25519 keypair\n(signing)
newDev -> newDev : Generate ECDH P-256 keypair\n(key exchange)

newDev -> newDev : Export ECDH public key
newDev --> userNew : Show device public key\n(QR code or base64)

note right of newDev
    **New Device Keys:**
    - deviceSignKeyPair (Ed25519)
    - deviceEcdhKeyPair (P-256)

    Private keys not yet wrapped
    (no Master KEK yet)
end note

== Step 2: Authorize on Existing Device ==

userNew -> userExisting : Share public key\n(scan QR / paste)
userExisting -> existingDev : Add new device

existingDev -> existingDev : Verify user owns\nexisting device (unlock)

existingDev -> existingDev : Get Vault Key from memory

existingDev -> existingDev : Create ECDH Key Slot\nfor new device
note right of existingDev
    **ECDH-ES+A256KW:**
    1. Generate ephemeral P-256 keypair
    2. ECDH: ephemeral.priv + newDevice.pub
    3. ConcatKDF(shared) -> KEK
    4. AES-KW wrap Vault Key
end note

existingDev -> existingDev : Add key slot to vault
existingDev -> existingDev : Sign updated envelope
existingDev -> s3 : Upload updated vault

existingDev --> userExisting : Device authorized

== Step 3: New Device Unlocks ==

userNew -> newDev : Enter Master Password / Recovery Key
newDev -> newDev : Derive KEK

newDev -> s3 : Download vault
s3 --> newDev : Signed envelope with\nnew device's key slot

newDev -> newDev : Find own key slot\n(by deviceId)
newDev -> newDev : ECDH decrypt key slot
note right of newDev
    **Unwrap Vault Key:**
    1. ECDH: own.priv + slot.epk
    2. ConcatKDF(shared) -> KEK
    3. AES-KW unwrap -> Vault Key
end note

newDev -> newDev : Decrypt vault with Vault Key
newDev -> newDev : Wrap device private keys\nwith Master KEK
newDev -> newDev : Store wrapped keys in IndexedDB

newDev --> userNew : Setup complete!\nVault accessible

legend right
    **Key Slot Structure:**
    {
      type: "device",
      deviceId: "uuid",
      alg: "ECDH-ES+A256KW",
      epk: { kty, crv, x, y },
      apu: "base64url",
      apv: "base64url",
      ciphertext: "wrapped_vault_key"
    }
endlegend

@enduml
